        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4107.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Royal Prussian Academy of Sciences</ref> in Berlin was founded in 1700. The list of corresponding members was limited to 200. For an account of the academy and its history, see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_3365.xml" resp="#automat" cert="low">Harnack 1900</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2"><ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1507.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Johann Franz Encke</ref> was professor of astronomy at the academy and at the University of Berlin, and director of the Berlin observatory (<hi rend="italic">DSB</hi>).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f3">The comparative anatomist and microscopist <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1480.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Christian Gottfried Ehrenberg</ref> was professor of medicine at the University of Berlin (<hi rend="italic">DSB</hi>). He corresponded with CD between 1844 and 1846 (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 3).</note>
        </div>        
            
